Words separated by non-space characters such a \ and / are concatenated together instead of being indexed into seperate words.

For example, a page containing the line '\Documents\Atlassian.doc' is returned when searching for 'DocumentsAtlassian' but not for 'Atlassian'. It is more natural to index the line as 'Documents' 'Atlassian' 'doc' instead of 'DocumentsAtlassian' 'doc'

