We would very much welcome few new features in the {recently-updated} tag. This tag has become a key feature of our enterprise wiki, to give the teams overview of the activities within, not only the whole spaces, but within certain areas.

The labels are good, but we cant count on it for this use - as some pages can be missed, etc. This feature improvement is very much based on the features of the Metadata plugin.

What we propose are options like;
{recently-updated:root=@self|pages=@children}
The root would specify a set of pages to include. When used in combination with the 'pages' option, allows children of a particular page. Use @self for the current page (the default), @parent for the parent page, or the name of any page, e.g MySpace:MyPage. If this is specified and the pages option is not, then the report will run over only the pages listed here.

The add-page macro makes trouble when adding a page while the parent page has german umlauts in the title AND a template is defined. Without the template everything works fine.

This works fine:
{add-page:parent=Döner}Click to add page{add-page}

This fails:
{add-page:template=My Template|parent=Döner Page}Click to add page{add-page}

